.TH SIMPLE SHELL 1 "NOVEMBER 2018" SIMPLE SHELL "simple shell User Manual"
.SH NAME
simple shell \- building a shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B
#include "shell.h"
.B

command [options] [file]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple shell
is a custom version of a command language interpreter that
executes commands read from the standard input or from a file.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP -i
If the -i option is present, the shell is interactive

.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.PP
.nf

To execute the shell:

./hsh

You can use the same syntax for running commands in other shells:

<command> <flags or options> <argument 1> <argument 2> ...

In non-interactive mode:

<command> | ./hsh

.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.PP
.NF

Interactive mode:

/bin/ls

Non-interactive mode:

echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.IP
.SH BUGS
Memory leaks and exit does not work

.SH AUTHOR
Michael Klein and Wendy Leung

.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR sh (1)
